HEADWORD: Long-sightedness
<hw>Long"-sight`ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state
or condition of being long-sighted; hence, sagacity;
shrewdness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>See
<er>Hypermetropia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

